You are working on a Vite multi-page frontend project.

Tech stack:
- Vite
- Tailwind CSS v4
- SCSS
- Handlebars partials
- Vanilla JavaScript modules

Project structure:

HTML pages are located in the project root.

Reusable components are in:
src/partials

JS entry point:
src/js/main.js

JS modules:
src/js/modules

Styles:
Tailwind base styles → src/styles/tailwind.css
Custom styles → src/styles/app.scss

Images:

Original images:
src/assets/img/raw

Optimized images:
src/assets/img/optimized

Rules:

Do not modify build configuration unless requested.

Do not replace Tailwind with other frameworks.

SCSS is used for custom styling.

Tailwind utilities may be used for layout and spacing.

Prefer semantic HTML.

Avoid unnecessary wrappers.

Keep JavaScript modular and place new scripts in src/js/modules.

Do not move project files or change architecture.

When creating reusable markup use Handlebars partials in src/partials.
